article.description: Jamaree Bouyea had 19 points as San Francisco topped Princeton 82-72 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Bouyea, Minlend carry San Francisco over Princeton 82-72
article.linkText: Bouyea, Minlend carry San Francisco over Princeton 82-72
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Jamaree Bouyea had 19 points as San Francisco topped Princeton 82-72 on Saturday night. Charles Minlend added 16 points, Jordan Ratinho and Jimbo Lull had 15 points apiece for the Dons (2-0). Lull led the team with 11 rebounds. Jaelin Llewellyn scored a career-high 24 points for the Tigers (0-2). Richmond Aririguzoh added 14 points and six boards. Drew Friberg had nine rebounds. Friberg, whose 19 points per game heading into the matchup led the Tigers, was held to only 5 points (1 of 10). San Francisco matches up against Yale at home on Monday. Princeton takes on Lafayette at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
